# Global Flutter agent reminder

- Repo map: `AGENTS.md`. System of record: `docs/`.
- Cold start: `AGENTS.md` -> `docs/agent_knowledge_base.md` -> `docs/ai_code_review_protocol.md`.
- Use `docs/agents_quick_reference.md` for command lookup only.

## Execution

- Default: Plan -> Execute -> Verify -> Report. Plan once. Ask only hard blockers.
- Proof-first: confidence from smallest honest repo entrypoint.

## Context budget

- Read smallest blocks needed; prefer targeted search + narrow reads.
- context ladder: map docs -> durable memory -> code-review-graph -> targeted raw files.
- Don’t restate policy; point to canon docs.

## Quality bar

- Default to smallest reversible change satisfying business goal + reliability bar.
- Don't change files until at least 95% confident in goal/scope/approach.
- Surgical diff: each changed line traces to request or required validation/doc update.
- Treat AI code as draft until problem-fit, simplification, security, performance, edge-case, error-pattern, dependency, naming, and testing review pass.
- Self-verify before report: request, changed files, proof, blockers, risk.

## Repo-first

- Prefer repo-local docs and shell entrypoints over host-specific shortcuts.
- Repeated failure => add missing repo capability: doc, fixture, test, script,
  route proof, log helper, validation check.
- File verified reusable conclusions into source doc, `docs/changes/`, `docs/plans/`, or `tasks/lessons.md`; don't leave chat-only.
- Agent/docs changes: semantic-lint stale plans, duplicate rules, source/host-template contradictions.
- For agent/docs changes, keep the map short and run `./tool/check_agent_knowledge_base.sh`.
- Agent behavior changes start in source docs, then sync both Codex and Cursor host templates; don't fork unless capabilities differ.
- Flutter widget tests: use `WidgetTester.view`; don't use deprecated `tester.binding.window` test-value APIs.
- Favor copy/paste-ready repo commands over long prose.
